  "texts": [
    "Progression of optical observations over the full KiDS survey, for pointings within the final 1347 deg 2 footprint.",
    "The total number of DR5 pointings is shown as the dashed grey line.",
    "The figure demonstrates the slow initial progress made by the survey, whereby only ∼5% of planned r-band observations were completed in the initial 18 months of datataking, prompting changes in the queuing of (in particular) the dark-time observations.",
    "Conversely, at the end of the survey, the complete secondpass of i-band observations (designated i 2) was completed in roughly the same time span.",
    "Fig. 5.5Fig."
